,"Epiblast forms all three germ layers and amniotic cavity"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe inner cell mass differentiates into two distinct layers during week two of development. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eepiblast\u003C/strong\u003E (dorsal layer) gives rise to all three germ layers (ectoderm, mesoderm, and endoderm) through gastrulation and forms the amniotic cavity. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile the \u003Cstrong\u003Ehypoblast\u003C/strong\u003E (ventral layer) forms the primary yolk sac and contributes to some extraembryonic tissues.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Bilaminar disc formation occurs during week two of development.","The epiblast gives rise to all three germ layers and amniotic cavity.","The hypoblast forms the yolk sac and contributes to extraembryonic tissues,"],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015.","Muhr J, Arbor TC, Ackerman KM. Embryology, Gastrulation. In: StatPearls [Online]. [Updated 2023 Apr 23]. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK554394/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48274"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15838"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48274","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48274"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-18T21:17:48+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-18T21:18:13+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8529"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62824"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"